Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.84,0:06:28.65,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,事故详情见av21807258 《空中浩劫S18E06：2014年维珍银河太空船2号解体事件》
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:37.63,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,拉倒吧早就咕到2020年后了
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.22,0:09:27.64,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,YouTuber口误 是“Delta IV” 不是“Delta V”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.92,0:09:41.96,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,（可以说是氢氧机里的天顶星科技）
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:12:04.73,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,详情见av14923456
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.34,0:12:08.83,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,接下来是狗尾续貂、跑题时间
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.08,0:12:35.79,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,大叔你这说的什么跟什么 跟标题有毛关系？
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.25,0:00:03.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每一代人都会重新定义宇宙的边界
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.25,0:00:03.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Each generation reinvents space as the cosmic frontier
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.24,0:00:06.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在加加林、薛帕德那个时代
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.24,0:00:06.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In the age of Gagarin and Shepard
Dialogue: 1,0:00:06.36,0:00:10.97,1080CN,,0,0,0,,试飞员总会向摄像机笑一笑来证明他们不是假人
Dialogue: 2,0:00:06.36,0:00:10.97,1080EN,,0,0,0,,test pilots grinned into the TV cameras to prove that they were made from the right stuff
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.45,0:00:16.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而到了2018年，造火箭却变成了身家亿万的投资商为所欲为之为所欲为的平台
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.45,0:00:16.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and in 2018, orbital space is becoming the playground for billionaire entrepreneurs
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.12,0:00:19.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,让他们儿时的梦想变为现实
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.12,0:00:19.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,turning their childhood dreams into reality
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.73,0:00:33.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,大家印象里，NASA的管理者都是一群老气横秋的人
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.73,0:00:33.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In this picture the administrators at NASA are the dull old guys in the
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.21,0:00:36.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,慢慢榨干政府给的钱
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.21,0:00:36.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,background dishing out most of the government money
Dialogue: 1,0:00:36.19,0:00:42.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,来签各种项目，每每问及他们都说“咕咕咕在做啦”
Dialogue: 2,0:00:36.19,0:00:42.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to established aerospace contractors, always seem to be under delivering and be behind schedule
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.15,0:00:46.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然有数十亿的资金，大家也都知道
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.15,0:00:46.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Despite the billions of dollars in funding, so the story goes
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.80,0:00:52.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但NASA让我们太失望了，没造成行星际飞船，月球基地也没信
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.80,0:00:52.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA has let us down by failing to build interplanetary spaceships or lunar bases
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.67,0:00:58.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,更甭想什么星际殖民防止地球再闹个物种灭绝之类的幺蛾子
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.67,0:00:58.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and no off world colonies have been established to protect us against accidental extinction
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.18,0:01:03.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以NASA真的如此效率低下吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.18,0:01:03.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But is it true that NASA works too slowly
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.34,0:01:07.37,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果是真的，那其他国家的航天企业咋还没打败NASA呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.34,0:01:07.37,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And if so why haven't they been beaten to the punch already?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.82,0:01:12.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那些私家飞船和私家空间站都哪去了？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.82,0:01:12.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Where are the privately funded spaceships or orbital stations?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.70,0:01:19.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉老总马一龙显然认为他的公司能打败NASA从而第一个送人类去火星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.70,0:01:19.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX's Elon Musk apparently believes his company can beat NASA to a manned landing of Mars
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.61,0:01:22.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但他也不是第一个有如此野心的人
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.61,0:01:22.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but he's not the first to have such grand ambitions
Dialogue: 1,0:01:23.45,0:01:27.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,仔细了解下NASA和美国几家私企的关系
Dialogue: 2,0:01:23.45,0:01:27.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A closer look at the relationship between NASA and private enterprise in America
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.25,0:01:32.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你会发现不知两家公司在比赛谁先去那颗红色星球
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.25,0:01:32.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,reveals that there is much more than a two horse race to the Red Planet
Dialogue: 1,0:01:32.73,0:01:36.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管航天的历史进程看上去像迈了几个大跨步
Dialogue: 2,0:01:32.73,0:01:36.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although space history sometimes feels like a series of giant leaps
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.94,0:01:42.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但屏幕能看到的部分不少都是他们为达到宣传目的而特意挑选的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.94,0:01:42.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the small steps that appear on our screens are largely selected to be good PR and marketing
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.18,0:01:46.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而不是真正想反映当前的航天科技水平
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.18,0:01:46.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,rather than a reflection of the current aerospace technology
Dialogue: 1,0:01:47.55,0:01:49.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA至今已经六十年了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:47.55,0:01:49.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA is 60 years old this year
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.95,0:01:55.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但其具体资金如何，还要看每个四年内的总统政府到底能给你多少
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.95,0:01:55.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but its annual budget depends on what it can deliver within each 4-year cycle of American politics
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.04,0:02:00.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,即便是大家都资瓷连任的总统也是如此
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.04,0:02:00.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,even if a president expects two terms in office
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.91,0:02:04.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,对于NASA超过八年才能见到成效的项目
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.91,0:02:04.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Any NASA project that takes longer than eight years to get results
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.13,0:02:10.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,要么让总统名垂青史，要么直接被毙了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.13,0:02:10.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,will either heap glory on his or her political opponents or face cancellation
Dialogue: 1,0:02:10.89,0:02:16.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,肯尼迪总统从宣布要送人去月球到实现用了七年
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.89,0:02:16.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,President John F Kennedy's commitment to send astronauts to the moon took seven years to achieve
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.73,0:02:20.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,即便当时NASA的经费（换算过来）是今天的八倍
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.73,0:02:20.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,even with funding at eight times what it is today
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.91,0:02:24.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,航天飞机也叫太空运输系统（STS）
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.91,0:02:24.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Space Shuttle also known as the Space Transportation System (STS)
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.02,0:02:30.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也是早在1968、69年，阿波罗任务刚载人飞行的时候就开始构思了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.02,0:02:30.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,was in planning when the first manned Apollo missions flew in 1968 and 69
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.00,0:02:38.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,七十年代早期，公众开始不愿意在航天上砸太多钱，航天飞机计划面临取消
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.00,0:02:38.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,By the early 1970s, public support for expensive projects was fading and the Space Shuttle faced cancellation
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.20,0:02:46.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,为了留住项目，NASA重新设计了可复用轨道器，使其不但能载平民，还可适配军方任务
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.20,0:02:46.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,To save the project, NASA redesigned the reusable orbiter to be able to fly both civilian and airforce missions
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.97,0:02:52.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,结果就是航天飞机极其复杂又昂贵
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.97,0:02:52.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The result was that the shuttle became hugely complicated cumbersome and expensive
Dialogue: 1,0:02:52.92,0:02:57.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,1981年首飞的时候，里根总统刚上任
Dialogue: 2,0:02:52.92,0:02:57.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When the first missions began in 1981 when Ronald Reagan entered office
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.87,0:03:00.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,发射任务就已经严重拖后了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.87,0:03:00.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the launch schedule was much slower than planned
Dialogue: 1,0:03:00.94,0:03:05.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,说好的一周一飞，变成了一年四飞
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.94,0:03:05.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The promised weekly flights became an average of just four missions per year
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.12,0:03:09.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然从今天来看还算是个不错的转变
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.12,0:03:09.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But by today's standards that seems like a decent turnaround
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.59,0:03:17.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA的航天飞机需要许多子系统的精准配合，它们被分配给几个不同的承包商
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.59,0:03:17.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA's Shuttle required the precise coordination of advanced subsystems, built by different contractors
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.56,0:03:22.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这当中一些著名的航天与防务部门贡献最大
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.56,0:03:22.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The largest contributions came from the famous names in Aerospace and Defense
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.49,0:03:26.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,轨道器是在加州帕姆代尔的北美罗克韦尔公司制造
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.49,0:03:26.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The orbiter was built in Palmdale California by North American Rockwell
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.81,0:03:32.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,发动机由洛克达因公司研发，外挂燃料箱来自马丁·玛丽埃塔公司
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.81,0:03:32.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The engines were developed by Aerojet Rocketdyne, the external tank was built by Martin Marietta
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.81,0:03:37.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,命运多舛的固推来自莫顿聚硫橡胶公司
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.81,0:03:37.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the ill-fated solid rocket boosters with a responsibility of Morton Thiokol
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.92,0:03:43.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果最开始航天飞机项目单独签给一家公司，那可能就和其他公司没关系了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.92,0:03:43.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,If the Space Shuttle had been built by any one corporation it would have probably put them out of business
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.35,0:03:48.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但通过NASA的航天飞机项目，美国政府建立起了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.35,0:03:48.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But through NASA, the US government was able to fund an
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.18,0:03:53.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在当时不太可能出现的、依靠当时全球最强经济体的技术联合体
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.18,0:03:53.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,unlikely combination of technologies using the power of the world's largest economy
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.27,0:03:57.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这样说来，航天飞机项目还算成功
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.27,0:03:57.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In those terms the Shuttle program was a success
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.03,0:04:03.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其作为一个先进的发射系统，服役了整整三十年
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.03,0:04:03.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,building, flying and servicing a pioneering launch system over three decades
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.68,0:04:09.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但不看好航天飞机的人认为，航天飞机的复杂设计让每次飞行都如履薄冰
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.68,0:04:09.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But to its critics, the compromised design made every mission a disaster waiting to happen
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.64,0:04:16.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,步入21世纪，航天飞机已到迟暮之年，美国急需新的发射系统
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.64,0:04:16.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,At the beginning of the 21st century the shuttle was shown its age and a new launch vehicle was desperately needed
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.64,0:04:21.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但研发进度大家都能想到，简直史无前例地慢
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.64,0:04:21.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But the development was, as you've guessed it, progressing even more slowly than ever
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.40,0:04:29.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2003年2月，哥伦比亚号航天飞机再入大气时解体，七人遇难
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.40,0:04:29.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In February 2003, the orbiter Columbia was destroyed on re-entry costing the lives of its seven crew members
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.25,0:04:36.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,事故调查期间美国的航天项目搁置两年
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.25,0:04:36.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,America's space program was grounded for two years whilst a thorough investigation was carried out
Dialogue: 1,0:04:37.13,0:04:44.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,同时，加州的一小队航天工程师正在微调他们新的可复用航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.13,0:04:44.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile in California a small team of aerospace engineers were fine-tuning their own reusable space plane
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.40,0:04:46.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可能搞一个世界级大新闻
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.40,0:04:46.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which were about to make world news
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.84,0:04:52.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,伯特·鲁坦的公司的缩尺复合体决定争夺Ansari X奖项
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.84,0:04:52.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Burt Rutan's company Scaled Composites was competing for the Ansari X Prize
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.41,0:04:56.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一千万美元奖励给第一个能在两周内发射两次高度超过100千米的飞船的非政府组织
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.41,0:04:56.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,worth $10 million to the first non-government organization
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.72,0:05:02.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一千万美元奖励给第一个能在两周内发射两次高度超过100千米的飞船的非政府组织
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.72,0:05:02.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to launch a spacecraft above 100km altitude twice within 2 weeks
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.65,0:05:06.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2004年9月29日和10月4日
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.65,0:05:06.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On September 29th and October the 4th 2004
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.36,0:05:12.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,鲁坦的太空船一号在白骑士号的携带下先后达到了102千米与115千米的高空
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.36,0:05:12.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Rutan's Spaceship One launched from White Knight to 102km and then a 115km
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.94,0:05:17.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,打破了40年前X-15飞机创下的纪录
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.94,0:05:17.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,flying higher than a record set by the X-15 40 years earlier
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.76,0:05:21.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也让太空船一号赢得了Ansari X奖
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.76,0:05:21.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and enabling Spaceship One to win the Ansari X PRIZE
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.40,0:05:29.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,英国企业家理查德·布兰森马上掏钱，想让太空船一号变成能进太空的商业坐骑
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.40,0:05:29.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,British entrepreneur Sir Richard Branson immediately set out to turn Spaceship One into a commercial ride into space
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.17,0:05:33.91,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并宣布在莫哈维沙漠建一个太空船发射、降落场
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.17,0:05:33.91,1080EN,,0,0,0,,announcing plans for a spaceport in Mojave Desert
Dialogue: 1,0:05:34.24,0:05:37.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,布兰森宣布他的新公司名字叫维珍银河
Dialogue: 2,0:05:34.24,0:05:37.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Branson initially said that his new company Virgin Galactic
Dialogue: 1,0:05:37.90,0:05:45.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,将在2007年进行亚轨道飞行，之后推到2009年
Dialogue: 2,0:05:37.90,0:05:45.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,would begin suborbital flights in 2007, but soon revised the date back to 2009
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.63,0:05:49.90,1080CN,,0,0,0,,船票卖的挺快，二十五万美元一张
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.63,0:05:49.90,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Seats began selling fast at a cool $250,000 each
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.25,0:05:54.06,1080CN,,0,0,0,,布兰森还弄来不少私人投资
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.25,0:05:54.06,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Branson also managed to secure vast sums in private funding
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.33,0:05:59.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,包括来自阿布扎比主权财富基金的三亿美元投资
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.33,0:05:59.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,including almost $300 million from Abu Dhabi Sovereign Wealth Fund
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.98,0:06:06.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但在幕后，太空船二号发动机升级的研发则非常缓慢
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.98,0:06:06.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,However behind the scenes development was progressing slowly on the engine for the updated Spaceship Two
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.68,0:06:12.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空船二号将采用基于过氧化物的火箭发动机，由内华达山脉公司制造
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.68,0:06:12.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a high test based peroxide rocket motor built by the aerospace company Sierra Nevada
Dialogue: 1,0:06:12.91,0:06:18.44,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在2014年10月，人们加深了对维珍银河公司的怀疑
Dialogue: 2,0:06:12.91,0:06:18.44,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Skepticism about Virgins ambitious schedule intensified in October 2014
Dialogue: 1,0:06:18.88,0:06:22.25,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空船二号——企业号试飞发生事故
Dialogue: 2,0:06:18.88,0:06:22.25,1080EN,,0,0,0,,when disaster struck a test flight of the VSS enterprise
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.84,0:06:28.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当飞船跨音速的时候，太空船二号的羽翼机构过早部署
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.84,0:06:28.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Whilst passing the speed of sound, the feather mechanism on a Spaceship Two was deployed too early
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.96,0:06:35.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,导致太空船二号在五万英尺高度解体，试飞员之一麦克遇难
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.96,0:06:35.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and the VSS Enterprise broke up at an altitude of 50,000 feet, and one of the pilots Michael Ellsbury was killed
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.59,0:06:44.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这次事故是灾难性的，尤其对于布兰森的太空旅行构想来说
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.59,0:06:44.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The accident was a catastrophe, not least for Branson's attempt to market Spaceship Two as the future of space tourism
Dialogue: 1,0:06:44.70,0:06:50.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管设计大改，维珍银河公司还是把工作重心转向了设计一些适中的项目
Dialogue: 2,0:06:44.70,0:06:50.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Despite major changes in the design, Virgin Galactic has shifted focus to more modest projects
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.00,0:06:56.28,1080CN,,0,0,0,,比如在改装后的747下放一个小型发射系统
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.00,0:06:56.28,1080EN,,0,0,0,,such as its small static launch system using a modified Boeing 747
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.68,0:06:59.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空新时代正在到来
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.68,0:06:59.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The era of new space was underway
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.29,0:07:05.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但其中的危险却贯穿整个载人航天的历史
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.29,0:07:05.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but for dangers were as real as they had been for the whole history of manned space flight
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.68,0:07:14.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2011年7月21日，亚特兰蒂斯号航天飞机在佛州肯尼迪航天中心最后一次着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.68,0:07:14.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On 21st of July 2011, the Space Shuttle Atlantis touched down for the last time at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida
Dialogue: 1,0:07:14.51,0:07:17.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从此美国没法送人进太空了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:14.51,0:07:17.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,leaving America without a manned space vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.04,0:07:23.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这一尴尬局面让NASA不得不求助俄罗斯
Dialogue: 2,0:07:18.04,0:07:23.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This embarrassing gap in capability would leave NASA dependent upon the Russians
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.26,0:07:29.79,1080CN,,0,0,0,,来送美国的宇航员去国际空间站，而俄罗斯也为此获利不少
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.26,0:07:29.79,1080EN,,0,0,0,,for getting its astronauts to and from the ISS and the Russians were making the most out of the situation
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.43,0:07:38.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2008年航天飞机还在的时候，俄罗斯向NASA的开价是每座位2160万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.43,0:07:38.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In 2008 when the shuttle was still around, Roscosmos charged NASA $21.6 million per seat
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.84,0:07:42.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但航天飞机退役后，船票就一路飙升
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.84,0:07:42.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but after the Shuttle was retired that price went up dramatically
Dialogue: 1,0:07:42.97,0:07:48.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用了快五十年的联盟号飞船的船票
Dialogue: 2,0:07:42.97,0:07:48.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The cost of a seat on the Russian Soyuz, a 50-year-old expendable vehicle
Dialogue: 1,0:07:48.52,0:07:55.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,到了2018年涨到了每座位8100万美元
Dialogue: 2,0:07:48.52,0:07:55.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but had outlived all of its competitors in 2018 is now $81 million
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.68,0:08:02.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA的下一代发射系统也是融合了两种退役的系统
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.68,0:08:02.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA's next-generation Launch System was also shaping up to be a combination of two retired systems
Dialogue: 1,0:08:02.48,0:08:10.88,1080CN,,0,0,0,,顶端飞船是类似阿波罗构型的，下面级则是类似航天飞机的橙罐加两个固推
Dialogue: 2,0:08:02.48,0:08:10.88,1080EN,,0,0,0,,An Apollo type command module atop of a Shuttle style orange fuel tank boosted by two solid fuel Rockets
Dialogue: 1,0:08:11.52,0:08:15.85,1080CN,,0,0,0,,被取消的星座计划中的战神火箭改了改
Dialogue: 2,0:08:11.52,0:08:15.85,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Adapted from the Ares rocket canceled from the Constellation Program
Dialogue: 1,0:08:16.14,0:08:21.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,变成了新的“太空发射系统”（SLS）
Dialogue: 2,0:08:16.14,0:08:21.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the new rocket went by the no frills name of a Space Launch System or SLS
Dialogue: 1,0:08:21.96,0:08:26.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,高111米，比土星五号高一点点
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.96,0:08:26.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,At 111m, the evolved SLS will be just a bit taller than the Saturn V
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.16,0:08:31.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但性能强多了，近地轨道运力130吨
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.16,0:08:31.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but more powerful and able to lift a 130 tons to low Earth orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.41,0:08:37.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,构型1将在不早于2019年的时间首飞
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.41,0:08:37.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The SLS will launch no sooner than 2019 beginning with block 1
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.88,0:08:44.52,1080CN,,0,0,0,,将把猎户座载人模块在内的70吨载荷送进近地轨道
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.88,0:08:44.52,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which will begin with a capacity of 70 tons payload including the manned Orion module to low Earth orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:08:45.45,0:08:48.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,波音负责造芯级
Dialogue: 2,0:08:45.45,0:08:48.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Boeing is commissioned to build the core stage
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.57,0:08:57.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,下面四台RS-25发动机由洛克达因公司升级，每台提供418,000磅（190吨）推力
Dialogue: 2,0:08:48.57,0:08:57.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,powered by four RS-25 engines, upgraded by Aerojet Rocketdyne to provide 418,000 pounds of thrust
Dialogue: 1,0:08:57.69,0:09:02.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,比其上次用于航天飞机的时候推力增加了5%
Dialogue: 2,0:08:57.69,0:09:02.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,a 5% increase in power from when they last flew on the Space Shuttle
Dialogue: 1,0:09:02.70,0:09:09.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,新的固推也在研制中，和航天飞机一样，交给轨道ATK公司来做
Dialogue: 2,0:09:02.70,0:09:09.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,New solid rocket boosters under development at the same company that built them for the Shuttle Orbital ATK
Dialogue: 1,0:09:09.40,0:09:15.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用于航天飞机上的四段固推被升级成五段
Dialogue: 2,0:09:09.40,0:09:15.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,have been upgraded from four segments in the shuttle boosters to a new five segment design
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.50,0:09:19.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,SLS的上面级也是从现有技术升级而来的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.50,0:09:19.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The SLS upper stage were also upgrade from existing technology
Dialogue: 1,0:09:20.22,0:09:27.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用的是ULA的Delta IV火箭的二级作为临时过渡用的低温推进系统
Dialogue: 2,0:09:20.22,0:09:27.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Taking United Launch Alliance's Delta IV second stage and adapting it to become the interim cryogenic propulsion stage
Dialogue: 1,0:09:28.14,0:09:32.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,使用单台RL-10发动机送载荷入轨
Dialogue: 2,0:09:28.14,0:09:32.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,using a single RL-10 engine to lift the payload into orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:09:33.44,0:09:37.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,RL-10发动机首次服役是在1962年
Dialogue: 2,0:09:33.44,0:09:37.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The RL-10 engine first saw service in 1962
Dialogue: 1,0:09:37.92,0:09:41.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,是美国最古老的氢氧火箭发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:09:37.92,0:09:41.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,making it America's oldest liquid hydrogen rocket engine
Dialogue: 1,0:09:42.60,0:09:47.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,按计划，当2022年SLS构型1B发射时
Dialogue: 2,0:09:42.60,0:09:47.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When the block 1b launches in 2022, according to current plans
Dialogue: 1,0:09:47.44,0:09:51.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它将使用更大的探险号上面级
Dialogue: 2,0:09:47.44,0:09:51.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it will be upgraded to the larger Exploration Upper Stage
Dialogue: 1,0:09:51.92,0:09:55.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,运力增加至近地轨道105吨
Dialogue: 2,0:09:51.92,0:09:55.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,increasing the payload capacity 105 tons to low Earth orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.19,0:10:03.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,使用四台RL-10C-3发动机，届时，RL-10系列发动机就真的是“花甲之年”了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.19,0:10:03.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,using four RL-10C-3 engines, and by then, the RL-10 will be a sixty-year-old design
Dialogue: 1,0:10:04.41,0:10:09.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,对于去月球和火星的比赛，乌龟和兔子谁赢还不好说
Dialogue: 2,0:10:04.41,0:10:09.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In the race to the moon and mars, the tortoise may eventually beat the hare
Dialogue: 1,0:10:09.95,0:10:16.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,紧跟NASA步伐，杰夫·贝索斯为蓝色起源选了座右铭“Gradatim Ferociter”
Dialogue: 2,0:10:09.95,0:10:16.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Taking NASA's approach, Jeff Bezos chose the motto for Blue Origin: "Gradatim Ferociter"
Dialogue: 1,0:10:16.75,0:10:19.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,意思是“一步一步前进,摆脱一切牵绊”
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.75,0:10:19.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which means step by step ferociously
Dialogue: 1,0:10:19.63,0:10:25.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们公司的徽章长这样，俩王八从佛州和加州起飞飞向宇宙
Dialogue: 2,0:10:19.63,0:10:25.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,To illustrate, the company's coat of arms bears a pair of giant tortoises on either side of America
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.95,0:10:30.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们公司的徽章长这样，俩王八从佛州和加州起飞飞向宇宙
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.95,0:10:30.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,climbing upwards from Florida and California towards other worlds
Dialogue: 1,0:10:31.31,0:10:36.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,贝索斯的公司拿着NASA的钱也在一步一步前进
Dialogue: 2,0:10:31.31,0:10:36.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Bezos's company has benefited from NASA investing in slow incremental development
Dialogue: 1,0:10:37.13,0:10:42.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尤其是在一些可靠、成熟技术专业知识的培养上
Dialogue: 2,0:10:37.13,0:10:42.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,not least in the way this has nurtured expertise in reliable, proven technologies
Dialogue: 1,0:10:43.23,0:10:47.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,一些航天与防务部门的大公司的工程师与技术人员
Dialogue: 2,0:10:43.23,0:10:47.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Engineers and technicians from the big Defense and Aerospace companies
Dialogue: 1,0:10:47.56,0:10:50.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,都想去太空叉和蓝源工作
Dialogue: 2,0:10:47.56,0:10:50.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,have been persuaded to move to SpaceX or Blue Origin
Dialogue: 1,0:10:51.12,0:10:55.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不但工资高，还有参与新的太空竞赛的魅力感
Dialogue: 2,0:10:51.12,0:10:55.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with lucrative salaries and the glamorous image of the new space movement
Dialogue: 1,0:10:56.28,0:11:02.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,不管这些工程师、科学家安身何处，NASA的赞助肯定从来不会缺席
Dialogue: 2,0:10:56.28,0:11:02.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Wherever these engineers and scientists are based, NASA awards funding in much the same way as he always has
Dialogue: 1,0:11:02.99,0:11:06.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,和往常一样，支持竞争对手之间的提议
Dialogue: 2,0:11:02.99,0:11:06.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,by backing proposals from the strongest competitors
Dialogue: 1,0:11:06.68,0:11:12.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而别看马一龙送假人进太空这事比贝索斯那傻屌座右铭更出名
Dialogue: 2,0:11:06.68,0:11:12.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,And although Elon Musk is more famous for putting crash-test dummies into orbit than writing mottos
Dialogue: 1,0:11:12.64,0:11:17.13,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉的可回收火箭也在不停迭代进步
Dialogue: 2,0:11:12.64,0:11:17.13,1080EN,,0,0,0,,his company SpaceX has also steadily iterated their fly back boosters
Dialogue: 1,0:11:17.52,0:11:23.56,1080CN,,0,0,0,,今年5月，可多次复用的构型5也成功发射了
Dialogue: 2,0:11:17.52,0:11:23.56,1080EN,,0,0,0,,towards the rapidly reusable block 5 due to launch for the first time in may 2018
Dialogue: 1,0:11:24.16,0:11:31.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,有了亿万富翁的资助，使得太空叉这样的公司真的敢随便炸火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:11:24.16,0:11:31.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,With a billionaire entrepreneur part funding the project, spectacular rapid unscheduled disassemblies
Dialogue: 1,0:11:31.34,0:11:37.16,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而像洛马、波音这样的公司就不敢这样乱尝试
Dialogue: 2,0:11:31.34,0:11:37.16,1080EN,,0,0,0,,have been more exceptabtle from a SpaceX brand than they would have been for ones like Lockheed Martin or Boeing
Dialogue: 1,0:11:37.63,0:11:44.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们在可靠性上的声誉可经不起几次试飞里的爆炸
Dialogue: 2,0:11:37.63,0:11:44.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,whose reputation for reliability depends upon avoiding the bad press of an exploding test flight
Dialogue: 1,0:11:45.16,0:11:51.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这是NASA这样的公共企业与私企之间新的合作关系带来的真正益处
Dialogue: 2,0:11:45.16,0:11:51.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is the real benefit that emerges from a new partnership of public and private space organizations
Dialogue: 1,0:11:52.01,0:11:57.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA通过支持一些投机的技术，可快可慢
Dialogue: 2,0:11:52.01,0:11:57.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA can be both fast and slow, supporting speculative technologies
Dialogue: 1,0:11:57.96,0:12:04.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,比如资助太空叉这样的公司，能把自己家火箭失败剪辑成NG集锦
Dialogue: 2,0:11:57.96,0:12:04.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,through companies like SpaceX, whose PR machine can turn a string of failures into a viral blooper reel
Dialogue: 1,0:12:05.34,0:12:08.83,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当私人太空旅行实现的时候，一定会引起全世界的关注
Dialogue: 2,0:12:05.34,0:12:08.83,1080EN,,0,0,0,,When private space tourism takes off the world will be watching
Dialogue: 1,0:12:09.08,0:12:13.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们也只能希望飞船的可靠性有所提升
Dialogue: 2,0:12:09.08,0:12:13.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and we can only hope that the spacecraft will be a reliable step forward
Dialogue: 1,0:12:13.50,0:12:17.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而不是真·送你上天
Dialogue: 2,0:12:13.50,0:12:17.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,rather than a dangerous detour on the way to a wider access to orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:12:18.33,0:12:22.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在一次大张旗鼓的首飞后，最有可能的是
Dialogue: 2,0:12:18.33,0:12:22.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After the first well-publicized flights, the likelihood is
Dialogue: 1,0:12:22.96,0:12:28.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空旅行的需求量暴涨，使得太空行业突然蓬勃发展
Dialogue: 2,0:12:22.96,0:12:28.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,that there will be more demand for out-of-this-world transport than any one company can meet
Dialogue: 1,0:12:29.08,0:12:35.79,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而其中更安全的公司，顾客也可能更青睐
Dialogue: 2,0:12:29.08,0:12:35.79,1080EN,,0,0,0,,A reputation for safety will win more customers than the boasts of those who cross the line first
